Citation.sAbstract: (Liquid-liquid) equilibrium (LLE) data of the solubility curves and tie-line compositions have been determined  for mixtures of (water + acetic acid + organic solvent (o-xylene, m-xylene or p-xylene)) at  T = 298.15 K and atmospheric pressure. The mixed isomers (xylenes) are also used as a mixed-solvent like  the individual isomers and phase behaviour of (water + acetic acid + xylenes) is investigated. The experimental  LLE data were correlated using the NRTL model, and the binary interaction parameters were  obtained. Distribution coefficients and separation factors have been evaluated for the immiscibility  region. The reliability of the experimental tie-lines has been confirmed by using Othmer Tobias  correlation.
Citation.sTitle: Phase behaviour of aqueous mixtures of acetic acid with isomers of xylene
